Figure 3. (a) Normalized TR-SFG difference spectra of CO stretching modes for the $\mathrm{Re}(\mathrm{CO})_{3} \mathrm{Cl}$ monolayer on gold surface at the indicated averaged delay times; (b) kinetics at $2021 \mathrm{~cm}^{-1}$ (GSB/SE for A'(1)), $1991 \mathrm{~cm}^{-1}$ (ESA for $A^{\prime}(1)$ ), and $1920 \mathrm{~cm}^{-1}$ (GSB/SE for low-frequency modes); (c) TR-IR absorption spectra of CO stretching modes of $\operatorname{Re}(\mathrm{CO})_{3} \mathrm{Cl}$ in MeCN at indicated averaged delay times; and (d) kinetics at indicated frequencies. Symbols represent experimental data; solid curves represent fits.

For comparison, we carried out TR-IR measurements for $\operatorname{Re}(\mathrm{CO})_{3} \mathrm{Cl}$ in three polar aprotic solvents and we analyzed the dependence of vibrational relaxation rates on the solvent. Figure 3c shows the transient IR absorption spectra of $\operatorname{Re}(\mathrm{CO})_{3} \mathrm{Cl}$ in acetonitrile (MeCN) under IR excitation at different delay times. The negative bands at $2029 \mathrm{~cm}^{-1}$ and positive bands at 2009 $\mathrm{cm}^{-1}$ are attributed to GSB/SE and ESA of the A'(1) mode, respectively. Similarly, the signals at lower frequency are attributed to GSB/SE and ESA of the A" and A'(2) modes, respectively. For the different GSB/SE and ESA patterns between TR-IR and TR-SFG spectra, there are two causes. First, the IR spectra are contributed from the imaginary part of $\chi^{(3)}$, while the SFG spectra contains both real and imaginary parts of $\chi^{(4)}$. Second, SFG signal is influenced by the molecular orientation of $\operatorname{Re}(\mathrm{CO})_{3} \mathrm{Cl}$ on gold surface. Figure $3 \mathrm{~d}$ shows the transient kinetics fitted by a biexponential decay. The $T_{1}$ lifetime of the $A^{\prime}(1)$ mode, which is used for further analysis, is found to be $30 \mathrm{ps}$. The $\mathrm{T}_{1}$ lifetime of the $\mathrm{A}^{\prime}(1)$ mode is found to be $23 \mathrm{ps}$ in acetone and $25 \mathrm{ps}$ in dimethylformamide (DMF), respectively (Table 1, SI). The $T_{1}$ lifetimes of the A"/A'(2) modes, which is close to that of $A^{\prime}(1)$ mode, are also listed in the Table 1 . The present results also show that $\tau_{v-v}$ for $\operatorname{Re}(\mathrm{CO})_{3} \mathrm{Cl}$ in bulk solution is shorter than that of $\operatorname{Re}(\mathrm{CO})_{3} \mathrm{Cl} / \mathrm{Au}$. As shown in Figures S3 and S4, the transient IR absorption spectra have similar features as those in MeCN except the GSB/SE signals for the A" and A'(2) modes that are more separated.

